Autopsy
Digital forensics platform for disk analysis

Forensics
Description
Autopsy is a digital forensics platform with GUI for analyzing hard drives and smartphones. It can recover deleted files, analyze browser history, and extract metadata.

Installation / Check
Check if installed:

which autopsy
Install command:

sudo apt install autopsy
Basic Syntax
autopsy (GUI application)
Common Commands
Command	What it does	When to use	Risk
autopsy

Launch Autopsy	Starting forensic analysis	
Create New Case

Start new investigation	Beginning new forensic case	
Add Data Source

Load disk image	Import evidence for analysis	
Run Ingest Modules

Analyze data	Extract and categorize evidence	
Step-by-Step Guide
1
Launch Autopsy
2
Create new case with details
3
Add disk image as data source
4
Run ingest modules (hash, keyword, etc.)
5
Browse results and timeline
6
Generate report
Understanding the Output
GUI shows file tree, deleted files, artifacts by category. Timeline view shows activity chronologically.

Important Warnings
•
Work on copies, never original evidence
•
Maintain chain of custody
•
Document all findings
•
Large images take time to process
⚠️ Use Kali Linux tools only on systems you own or have written permission to test. Unauthorized hacking is illegal and can result in criminal charges.
